Variable is a name of memory location or a container which holds value with it's data type

Ex:
int a = 10;



3 types of variables in java: 
	Local
		A variable declared inside the body of the method is called local variable

	Instance 
		A variable declared inside the class but outside the body of the method

	Static
		Declared as static is called static variable. 
		You can create a single copy of static variable and share among all the instances of the class.

2 types of data types in Java
	Primitive 
	Non-primitive.

